I like this approach of a builder that just collects all the entries and then builds the trie!
I don't so much like the interface name OpaqueIndex.   Why not just have it as part of Index:
public interface Index
{
    ...;
    class OpaqueBuilder
    {
        public static string Predicate<String> build();
    }
}

replies.bodyText:
I'm not yet decided about the Builders API, I'm considering merging them all into a single one. But the OpaqueIndex is needed because it exposes these two methods:
    boolean contains(String key);
    boolean contains(String key, int offset, int length);
and it could also expose some forms of boolean containsBest(...) in the future. But I'm not thrilled by this interface's name either.

